     <section style=" width: 100%;">
        <h2 class="title">JOB CATAGORIES</h2>

               <div class="Job_type">
                  <div class="Type">
                    <h3>Graphic Designer</h3>
                  </div>
                  <div class="Detail">
                    <p>
                      Graphic designers are responsible for creating visual concepts, using computer software or by hand, to communicate ideas that inspire, inform, or captivate consumers. They develop the overall layout and production design for advertisements, brochures, magazines, and corporate reports. Graphic designers must have strong artistic skills, excellent attention to detail, and the ability to work under tight deadlines.
                    </p>
                  </div>
                </div>

                <div class="Job_type">
                  <div class="Type">
                    <h3>Social Media Manager</h3>
                  </div>
                  <div class="Detail">
                    <p>A social media manager manages a business's social media accounts. They may create and curate content, respond to comments and messages, and develop social media marketing campaigns.
                    </p>
                  </div>
                </div>

               <div class="Job_type">
                  <div class="Type">
                    <h3>Mobile App Developer</h3>
                  </div>
                  <div class="Detail">
                    <p>A mobile app developer creates applications for mobile devices like smartphones and tablets. They may use programming languages like Java, Swift, or React Native. 
                    </p>
                  </div>
                </div>
            
              <div class="Job_type">
                  <div class="Type">
                    <h3>Web Developer</h3>
                  </div>
                  <div class="Detail">
                    <p> A web developer creates and maintains websites. They may work on the front-end (client-side) or back-end (server-side) of a website. They may use programming languages like HTML, CSS, JavaScript, and PHP.</p>
                  </div>
                </div>

              <div class="Job_type">
                  <div class="Type">
                    <h3>Software Engineer</h3>
                  </div>
                  <div class="Detail">
                    <p>
                      Software engineers are responsible for designing, developing, and maintaining software systems. They work closely with other members of their team to ensure that the software meets the requirements of the client or organization. Software engineers must have a strong understanding of programming languages and computer science principles, as well as excellent problem-solving and communication skills.
                    </p>
                  </div>
                </div>

                <div class="Job_type">
                  <div class="Type">
                    <h3>Marketing Specialist</h3>
                  </div>
                  <div class="Detail">
                    <p>
                      Marketing specialists are responsible for developing and implementing marketing strategies to promote a product or service. They conduct market research to identify target audiences, create advertising and promotional materials, and analyze the effectiveness of their campaigns. Marketing specialists must have excellent communication and analytical skills, as well as a strong understanding of consumer behavior and market trends.
                    </p>
                  </div>
                </div>

                <div class="Job_type">
                  <div class="Type">
                    <h3>Accountant</h3>
                  </div>
                  <div class="Detail">
                    <p>
                      Accountants are responsible for managing financial records and ensuring that they are accurate and up-to-date. They prepare financial reports, analyze financial data, and provide recommendations for improving financial performance. Accountants must have strong analytical skills, attention to detail, and the ability to communicate effectively with clients and colleagues.
                    </p>
                  </div>
                </div>

                <div class="Job_type">
                  <div class="Type">
                    <h3>Customer Service Representative</h3>
                  </div>
                  <div class="Detail">
                    <p>
                      Customer service representatives are responsible for providing assistance and support to customers who have questions, concerns, or complaints about a product or service. They interact with customers through various channels, such as email, phone, or social media, and work to resolve issues in a timely and efficient manner. Customer service representatives must have strong communication and problem-solving skills, as well as the ability to work well under pressure.
                    </p>
                  </div>
                </div>

